1. The 0/1 Knapsack problem aims to select items with given weights and profits to maximize total profit
  without exceeding the capacity (W) of the knapsack.
2. Each item can be taken either 0 or 1 time, not fractionally.
3. DP is used because the problem shows overlapping subproblems.
4. Condition:
  For each item i:
    If weight of item â‰¤ current capacity
        dp[i][w] = max( profit[i] + dp[i-1][w - weight[i]], dp[i-1][w] )
    Else (item too heavy):
        dp[i][w] = dp[i-1][w]
